# Blood Donation App

## Overview
The Blood Donation App is a mobile application designed to facilitate the connection between blood donors and recipients. The application streamlines the process of finding and donating blood, ensuring timely assistance for individuals in need.

## Features
- User Authentication: Secure login and registration system.
- Donor Registration: Enables users to register as blood donors.
- Recipient Requests: Allows users to request blood donations.
- Search Functionality: Users can search for available donors or recipients.
- Notifications: Alerts users regarding donation requests and confirmations.
- Profile Management: Users can update personal and medical information.

## Technologies Used
- Programming Language: Java
- Development Environment: Android Studio
- Database: Firebase (for authentication and data storage)

## Installation
To set up the project locally:

1. Clone the repository:
   git clone https://github.com/Abubakr-133/Blood-Donation-APP.git
2. Open the project in Android Studio.
3. Ensure that all required SDKs and dependencies are installed.
4. Build and run the project on an emulator or physical device.

## Usage
- Registration: New users can register as donors or recipients.
- Login: Existing users can log in to access their profiles.
- Dashboard: View and manage donation requests and offers.
- Settings: Update personal information and notification preferences.

